data.title: Relative values: Roberta Taylor and her brother, Bill

data.text:
BILL: My mum used to scrub floors in pubs, so Robbie was often a full-time baby-sitter. She was both my big sister and a little mother. We grew up in Millwall [in London's Isle of Dogs] in the early 1960s, where it was back-to-back houses and flats where everyone knew everyone else.

My dad was a gambler who left home when I was little. Robbie was more upset than I was, but for me, Dad just wasn't there. Robbie took me to my weekly appointments at Moorfields Eye Hospital. And she did all the fighting to protect me.
